-- Turkey's Akbank mandates for lira bonds of up to 10 billion lira
-- By Ece Toksabay
-- Tue Jun 24, 2014 10:11AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, June 24 (Reuters) - Turkish lender Akbank <AKBNK.IS> said on Tuesday it has mandated work on issuing bonds of worth a total of up to 10 billion lira ($4.68 billion).

The bank said in a statement to the Istanbul stock exchange that the maturities would be maximum 5 years.